definition.value: The oceanic division completely in Earth's southern hemisphere encircling Antarctica, comprising the southernmost waters of the World Ocean south of 60degS latitude. However, the Southern Ocean's northern boundary is not precise. Instead, the Antarctic Convergence, an ocean zone which fluctuates seasonally, separates the Southern Ocean from other oceans. This dynamic, natural boundary is formed by the convergence of two circumpolar currents, one easterly flowing and one westerly.

A current in the Southern Ocean, that is not part of the west wind drift. The Antarctica shelf and the sea-bottom ridges cause turbulence in the water and the west wind drift may get weaker in such areas. This can be seen even at the ocean surface, reversing the normally observed easterly water movement.
An ocean current that flows from west to east around Antarctica.
One of the 22 regions of Chad and its capital is Pala. It is composed of part of the former prefecture of Mayo-Kebbi (sub-prefectures of Pala and Lere).
One of the 22 regions of Chad and its capital is Sarh.

A department in the north central part of Guatemala. The capital and chief city of the department is Coban. Verapaz is bordered to the north by El Peten, to the east by Izabal, to the south by Zacapa, El Progreso, and Baja Verapaz, and to the west by El Quiche.
A department in Guatemala. The capital is Salama.
A department of Guatemala. The capital is Chimaltenango.
A department of Guatemala.

A region that includes Australia, the island of New Guinea (including Papua New Guinea and the Indonesian province of Papua), and the eastern part of the Indonesian archipelago, including the island of Sulawesi, the Moluccan islands (the Indonesian provinces of Maluku and North Maluku) and islands of Lombok, Sumbawa, Sumba, Flores, and Timor, often known as the Lesser Sundas.
A region that includes Africa south of the Sahara Desert, the southern and eastern fringes of the Arabian Peninsula, the island of Madagascar, and the islands of the western Indian Ocean.
A region that includes the Pacific Ocean islands of Micronesia, the Fijian Islands, and most of Polynesia (with the exception of New Zealand).

A region that includes Antarctica and several island groups in the southern Atlantic and Indian Oceans, including South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands, South Orkney Islands, the South Shetland Islands, Bouvet Island, the Crozet Islands, Prince Edward Islands, Heard Island, the Kerguelen Islands, and the McDonald Islands.
A region that extends from the Makran region of southern Pakistan through the Indian subcontinent and Southeast Asia to lowland southern China, and through Indonesia as far as Java, Bali, and Borneo.
A region that includes South America, Central America, and the Caribbean.

A continent that is surrounded by the Mediterranean Sea to the north, the Suez Canal and the Red Sea to the northeast, the Indian Ocean to the southeast, and the Atlantic Ocean to the west. There are 46 countries including Madagascar, and 53 including all the island groups.

A continent of the Americas, situated entirely in the Western Hemisphere and mostly in the Southern Hemisphere, with about a quarter in the Northern Hemisphere. It is bordered on the west by the Pacific Ocean and on the north and east by the Atlantic Ocean. North America and the Caribbean Sea lie to the northwest.

The convention used in gaz.obo is that the Europe-Asia boundary follows the watershed of the Ural Mountains from near Kara, Russia on the Kara Sea to the source of the Ural River, then follows that river to the Caspian Sea. The border then follows the watershed of the Caucasus Mountains from the Caspian Sea to the Black Sea.
The sum of the Nearctic and Palearctic Regions.
The Earth's southernmost continent, overlying the South Pole. It is situated in the southern hemisphere, almost entirely south of the Antarctic Circle, and is surrounded by the Southern Ocean.
A grouping term including Australia, New Zealand, the southwestern islands of the Pacific Ocean and the eastern islands of the Australasian Mediterranean Sea.
A department in Guatemala. The capital is Guastatoya and the largest city is Sanarate.
One of the 22 departments of Guatemala. The capital is the city of Escuintla.

One of the 22 departments of Guatemala. It bounds to the north with Mexico; to the east with Quiche, to the south with Totonicapan and San Marcos, and to the west again with Mexico. The capital is the city of Huehuetenango.

One of the 22 departments of Guatemala. Izabal is bordered to the north by Belize, to the north east by the Gulf of Honduras, and to the east by Honduras, and by the Guatemalan departments of Peten to the north west, Alta Verapaz to the west, and Zacapa to the south.
A department of Guatemala, in the south east of the republic. The capital is the city of Jalapa.
A department of Guatemala that borders along El Salvador and the Pacific Ocean. The capital is the city of Jutiapa.
A department of the nation of Guatemala.
A department in Guatemala. The capital is the city of Quetzaltenango.
A department of Guatemala. Located to the north-west of Guatemala City. The capital is Santa Cruz del Quiche.
A department located in the south-west of Guatemala, extending from the mountains to the Pacific Ocean coast. The capital is the city of Retalhuleu.
One of the 22 departments of Guatemala. The capital of Sacatepequez is Antigua Guatemala.
